    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-02-26T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-02-26T05:00:00-05:00" n="85"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                <head>85. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d85fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 751K.00/1-2662. Secret; Priority. A note on the source text in
                            <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">U. Alexis Johnson</persName>ʼs handwriting
                        reads: “No action required. Shown to Gov. <persName corresp="#p_HWA2"
                            >Harriman</persName>.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-02-26T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1962—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1088. Eyes only Secretary from <persName corresp="#p_NFEJ1">Nolting</persName>.
                    Ref <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1015.<note n="2" xml:id="d85fn2">
                        <ref target="#d82">Document 82</ref>.</note> Thank you for your message. I
                    shall proceed on basis you outline, and am confident Gen. <persName
                        corresp="#p_HGPD1">Harkins</persName> and I can work together successfully
                    assuming <pb facs="0196" n="176" xml:id="pg_176"/> our respective day-to-day
                    instructions are consistent. In this connection, the more we can think and speak
                    of Viet-Nam struggle in its present phase in terms of “pacification of the
                    country and winning the allegiance of the people” as contrasted with “winning
                    the war”, the more we will find success, in my judgment.</p>
                <p>I appreciate very much the Presidentʼs and your own expressions of confidence,
                    and warmly reciprocate them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NFEJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Nolting</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
